        </div>
        <div class="beginner-note-content">
            <h4>Welcome to Database Relationships!</h4>
            <p><strong>Don't worry if this sounds complex at first!</strong> Database relationships are just ways to <strong>connect different pieces of data</strong> in your application.</p>
            <p>Think of it like this: In real life, people have relationships (friends, family, coworkers). In databases, data has relationships too!</p>
            <p><strong>Focus on understanding:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>The concept:</strong> How different types of data connect to each other</li>
                <li><strong>The why:</strong> Why we need relationships instead of putting everything in one big table</li>
                <li><strong>The basics:</strong> The 3 main types of relationships (we'll explain them simply!)</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Remember:</strong> With C# and Entity Framework, you work with <strong>C# objects</strong> that automatically handle these relationships for you!</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- IMPORTANT NOTE ABOUT CODE SECTIONS -->
